The paper proposes a new framework for unsupervised feature learning for visual object recognition tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the framework involves a multi-layer architecture and sparse coding, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of spatial smoothness information, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
